This paper discusses active learning techniques for machine learning algorithms, specifically for feedforward neural networks, mixtures of Gaussians, and locally weighted regression. These topics are all related to statistical modeling and optimization, which are commonly studied in the computer science sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
